# Multilingual UI (en / fr / he / zh)

All user-visible text must be available in all four supported locales.

## Supported locales

Use the existing `Language` type: `en`, `fr`, `he`, `zh`. Do not add other languages without updating the type and all dictionaries.

## Translation source

- Import `usePreferences()` and call `t('key')` for every user-visible string: labels, buttons, toasts, errors, placeholders, tooltips, page titles, and metadata.
- Dictionary lives in `frontend/src/components/PreferencesContext.tsx`.
- When adding a key, add it to **all four** locale objects (`en`, `fr`, `he`, `zh`) in the same edit.

## Forbidden patterns

```tsx
// BAD — hardcoded English
<button>Export PDF</button>

// BAD — fallback masks missing keys
{t('confirm') || 'Confirm'}

// GOOD
<button>{t('exportPdf')}</button>
// + add exportPdf (and confirm if needed) to en/fr/he/zh blocks
```

- No hardcoded UI strings in JSX, props, or alerts.
- No `{t('x') || 'Fallback'}` — add the key to all locales instead.

## Dynamic text

- Use template keys with placeholders (e.g. `deleteTemplateConfirm: "Delete {name}?"`) and extend `t()` to accept optional params: `t('deleteConfirm', { name })`.
- Never duplicate English in confirm dialogs when a translation key already exists.

## Hebrew RTL

- Set `dir={lang === 'he' ? 'rtl' : 'ltr'}` on page shells (see `LayoutWrapper.tsx`).
- Update root `<html lang={lang}>` in `layout.tsx` when language changes.
- Apply RTL to login and all standalone pages, not only the authenticated shell.

## Dates and numbers

Pass the user's locale to formatting calls:

```tsx
date.toLocaleDateString(lang)
date.toLocaleString(lang)
```

## Backend errors

Map API error codes or known messages client-side via `t()`. Do not display raw Go error strings from the API.

## Review checklist

Before finishing frontend UI work:

1. Grep changed files for quoted strings outside `t()` calls.
2. Verify new keys exist in all four locale blocks.
3. Confirm Hebrew pages set `dir` correctly.
